three-room house where <PERSON> Faraj </PERSON> lived with his 60-year-old mother. An almond tree, a plum tree and a rose <PERSON> bush </PERSON> were left standing in the yard. The army said <PERSON> Faraj </PERSON> was detained several times previously for alleged participation in anti-Israeli disturbances. The tree-planting ceremony in <LOCATION> Beita </LOCATION> was organized by the `` Committee for <PERSON> Beita </PERSON>,'' a group trying to force authorities to make reparations to villagers whose homes were destroyed or damaged by the army as punishment. Jewish settlers and the army initially blamed the villagers for the death of Israeli <PERSON> Tirza </PERSON> <PERSON> Porat </PERSON> in the April clash, but an army report later determined she was accidentally killed by a bullet fired by an Israeli guarding the group.
