said he is being cautious until his fingerprints are checked Monday against those of <PERSON> Moses </PERSON> and <PERSON> Shawper </PERSON>. Doctors at a local mental health center who see <PERSON> Jackson </PERSON> twice a week say that since he suffered no physical trauma, he might have suffered an emotional one. `` So I'll remember and I wo n't like what I remember, or I wo n't ever remember and I wo n't like that, either,'' <PERSON> Jackson </PERSON> said It is not a pleasant choice, `` but I would prefer to be me,'' he said. `` There are nights when I lie awake at night thinking, and there's nothing to think about.''
