<HEAD>Senate Subcommittee Agrees To Spend $7.5 Million For Programming
To Cuba</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By DEBORAH MESCE</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 From a blimp floating over the <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Keys </LOCATION>, a proposed <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> government television service would beam a daily diet of <LOCATION> American </LOCATION> news shows, sitcoms and soap operas to the people of <LOCATION> Cuba </LOCATION>. A <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> Appropriations subcommittee on Friday agreed to spend $ 7.5 million to start a TV version of the <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Information </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Agency </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> 's </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Radio </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Marti </ORGANIZATION>, which has been broadcasting to <LOCATION> Cuba </LOCATION> since May 1985 `` We want to accelerate the free flow of information to our friends in <LOCATION> Cuba </LOCATION> and we want to send the message of democracy to everyone on the island,'' said Sen. <PERSON> Ernest </PERSON> <PERSON> Hollings </PERSON>, <LOCATION> D-S.C. </LOCATION>, chairman of the <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> panel that agreed to add the funds to <ORGANIZATION> USIA </ORGANIZATION>'s 1989 budget The <ORGANIZATION> USIA </ORGANIZATION> budget is to be considered by the full committee on Thursday next week. Cuban-Americans have been pushing the project as a natural and more effective follow-up to the radio service that is named for <LOCATION> Cuban </LOCATION> patriot <PERSON> Jose </PERSON> <PERSON> Marti </PERSON> and devotes its air time to promoting the cause of freedom in <LOCATION> Cuba </LOCATION>. `` TV <PERSON> Marti </PERSON> would be a much more powerful medium'' for informing Cubans about world events as well as what is happening in their own country, said <PERSON> Jorge </PERSON> <PERSON> Mas </PERSON> <PERSON> Canosa </PERSON>, chairman of the presidential advisory board for <ORGANIZATION> Radio </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Marti </ORGANIZATION>. A program mix of American, Mexican and <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <L