 Here are some commodity price trends for the past week: Grain and soybean futures moved sharply higher on the <ORGANIZATION> Chicago </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Board </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Trade </ORGANIZATION>. Wheat for delivery in July settled Friday at $ 3.73 -RCB- a bushel compared with $ 3.62 -RCB- a week earlier; July corn advanced to $ 2.57 -RCB- a bushel from $ 2.34 -LCB-; July oats soared to $ 2.60 a bushel from $ 1.96 -LCB-; and July soybeans rallied to $ 8.84 a bushel from $ 8.49. Livestock and meat futures retreated on the <ORGANIZATION> Chicago </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Mercantile </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>. June live cattle fell to 72.32 cents a pound from 72.65 cents; August feeder cattle dropped to 75.25 cents a pound from 75.92 cents; June live hogs slipped to 51.15 cents a pound from 52.45 cents; and July frozen pork bellies plunged to 50.07 cents a pound from 55.55 cents. Precious metals futures fell steeply on the <ORGANIZATION> Commodity </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>. August gold settled Friday at $ 453.30 a troy ounce compared with $ 469.30; July silver dropped to $ 7.015 a troy ounce from $ 7.270. Energy futures slid lower on the <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Mercantile </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>. West Texas Intermediate crude oil for July delivery fell to $ 16.73 a barrel from $ 17.50; July heating oil slumped to 44.25 cents a gallon from 47.13 cents; and July heating oil slipped to 49.22 cents a gallon from 50.89 cents.
